Name: Tsygan
Notes: Adopted as a pet by Soviet physicist Anatoli Blagonravov

Name: ZIB
Notes: An untrained street dog found running around the barracks, captured after Bobik ran away days before his flight.

Name: Laika
Notes: Also known as Kudryavka (Little Curly) and Limonchik (Little Lemon) and Zhuchka (Little Beetle) and also Muttnik

Name: Kusachka / Otvazhnaya
Notes: Made the most flights of any space dog.

Name: Strelka
Notes: Went on to have six puppies with a male dog named Pushok who participated in many ground-based space experiments, but never made it into space. One of the pups was named Pushinka (Пушинка, "Fluffy") and was presented to President John F. Kennedy by Nikita Khrushchev in 1961. A Cold War romance bloomed between Pushinka and a Kennedy dog named Charlie, resulting in the birth of four pups that JFK referred to jokingly as pupniks. Two of their pups, Butterfly and Streaker were given away to children in the Midwest. The other two puppies, White Tips and Blackie, stayed at the Kennedy home on Squaw Island but were eventually given away to family friends.

Name: Shutka
Notes: Also known as Damka (Little Lady) and Zhemchuzhina (Pearl). Adopted by Oleg Gazenko, a leading Soviet space scientist. She went on to have puppies and continued living with Gazenko and his family until her death 14 years later.

Name: Kometka
Notes: Also known as Krasavka (Cheater) and Zhulka (Beauty) and Zhemchuzhnaya (Pearly) and Snezchinka (Snowflake)
